io.grpc

Class Context.CancellableContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.grpc.Context
      • io.grpc.Context.CancellableContext
  • Enclosing class:
    Context

    public static final class Context.CancellableContext
extends Context
    A context which inherits cancellation from its parent but which can also be independently cancelled and which will propagate cancellation to its descendants.

        Description copied from class: Context
        Attach this context to the thread and make it Context.current(), the previously current context is returned. It is allowed to attach contexts where Context.isCancelled() is true.

      • detach

        public void detach(Context toAttach)
        Description copied from class: Context
        Detach the current context from the thread and attach the provided replacement. If this context is not Context.current() a SEVERE message will be logged but the context to attach will still be bound.

      • attachAsCloseable

        public Closeable attachAsCloseable()
        Attach this context to the thread and return a AutoCloseable that can be used with try-with-resource statements to properly attach the previously bound context when AutoCloseable.close() is called.
        Returns:
        a Closeable which can be used with try-with-resource blocks.

      • cause

        @Nullable
public Throwable cause()
        Description copied from class: Context
        If a context Context.isCancelled() then return the cause of the cancellation or null if context was cancelled without a cause. If the context is not yet cancelled will always return null.

        The cause is provided for informational purposes only and implementations should generally assume that it has already been handled and logged properly.

        Overrides:
        cause in class Context
